{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"92dda1c5-af2e-4a43-b6f0-205141b5b4b8","content":"Here's what to change:\n\n1. **Update the adapter** — upgrade `NUnit3TestAdapter` to **4.6.0+** (you're already there).\n\n2. **Add the platform package**:\n   ```xml\n   <PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Platform\" Version=\"1.5.3\" />\n   ```\n\n3. **Enable the new platform** in your `.csproj`:\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n4. **Remove** `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` — it's the VSTest entry point and is replaced by the new platform.\n\n5. **Run tests** with:\n   ```bash\n   dotnet test\n   ```\n   Or use the new native runner directly:\n   ```bash\n   dotnet run -- --help\n   ```\n\n**Optional but recommended**:\n- Add `<GenerateEntryPoint>true</GenerateEntryPoint>` if you want to use the project as a standalone executable test host.\n- Add `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport` if you need TRx output.\n- Add `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage` for coverage.\n\n> **Note:** Some VSTest-specific `.runsettings` features or custom adapters may need adjustment. The new platform uses a different extension model.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"5c10fb35-cb88-4465-9c60-4a5271bc6826","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating an NUnit test project from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. This is a knowledge question - I don't need to look at any code. Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":405,"requestId":"4C1B:7C3A8:D6DCA2:10AC384:6A012962"},"id":"dcc45f28-4267-48e8-b47d-a5a5120ff848","timestamp":"2026-05-11T00:57:16.171Z","parentId":"92244896-4a90-4401-9c64-2af6e89654f7"}
